    <p>Dr. Aseem Malhotra is a British cardiologist who has become one of the most outspoken critics of over-medication in cardiology. He argues that the medical profession has been "inadvertently harming patients" by over-prescribing medications while ignoring the root causes of heart disease - particularly diet and lifestyle factors.</p>

    <p>His work has been both influential and controversial, challenging pharmaceutical industry practices and calling for diet to be the first-line treatment for metabolic disease.</p>
